Structure of ORC file
========================
1. Header
2. Body --> Stripes-->row group
3. Tail

1. Header :-
		"ORC" is wrriten in these to know it is ORC file.

2. Body :- Body is made of stripes of data. These stripes further divied into block of records by default there are 10000 rows are there  in each  block(row group)
	   Default size of stripes is 250mb
	   stripes are further divied into row grop.Each row group holds 10000 rows by default.
	   ex. if you have 500mb orc file then there is 2 stripes of 250mb each.
		and if in each stripe of 250mb if there are 1 lakh records.Then these will divide into 10 row group each row group has 10000 records.
		1 orc file
		2 stripe in body of file
		each strip has 10 row group

	   Stripe structure 
	===========================
	1. set of index :- max & min & count for each column in every row group  in the stripe
			   Ex.   stripe 1: rowgroup 1: empid min 102 max 300
				 stripe 1: rowgroup 2: empid min 700 max 900

		Indexes are at 3 level:-
			1. File level  (Min and Max for entire file)
					statistics about the values in each column across the entire file
			2. stripe level (Min and Max for each stripe)
				- statistics about the values in each column for each stripe
			3. row level
				statistics about the values in each column for each set of 10,000 rows within a stripe.
		Note :- File level and stripe level index is stored in file footer.And row level is kept in index data of stripes.
	2. the data itselt broken into row group
	3. stripe footer :- It holds encodeing information

3. Tail
     It consist of 2 parts :-
	1. file footer :- 
			It contain meta data at file level.( meta data of whole orc file )
			Also it contain stripe level min and max.
			File level and stripe level index is stored in file footer.
	2. postscript:-
			It store which type of encodeing is used.
			It not in compressed  form.
			It helps to understand remaing part of file.

The file and stripe level column statistics are in the file footer so that they are easy to access to determine if the rest of the file needs to be read at all. 
Row level indexes include both the column statistics for each row group and the position for seeking to the start of the row group. 
The process of reading an ORC file works backwards through the file. The ORC reader reads the last 16k bytes of the file with the hope that it will contain both the Footer and Postscript sections.
A drawback of ORC was that it was designed specifically for Hive, and was not a general-purpose storage format that can be used with non-Hive MapReduce interfaces such as Java. However now lot of these shortcomings are covered now.

How  orc file is read internally?
step 1: It check header  is there "ORC" written.
step 2: If ORC in header then go to postscript where encoding info is stored. 
	   Based on encoding decrypt(un-encode/uncompress) the file footer.
step 3: read the file footer and get to know what is stored in which stripe and go to that stripe. 


